                           <p>
                           
                           
                           
                           Extant quires are mostly of 8 leaves each.
                                        
                           
                           
                           
                           Quires marked by catchwords at the end, in the middle
                                        of lower margins (only few of them has been preserved).
                                    
                        
                        
                        
                        </p>
                        </collation>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           <p>Columns: 2;
                                                  ruled lines: 19;
                                                  written lines: 19; Hair-side
                                        and flesh-side of folios distinguishable. Complete
                                        ruling by hard point, bifolium by bifolium on hair-side of
                                        folios. Pricking in outer margins only, quire by
                                        quire on verso. Each of the books of the Pentateuch
                                        commences a new leaf and Haftarot begin a new column.
                                        The first words of each pericope in the Pentateuch,
                                        Hafṭarot and Five Scrolls written in larger characters.
                                        The beginning of each pericope marked by פ פ פ.
                                        Last line written within ruling. Main text in
                                        two columns, commentary in outer and lower
                                    margins.</p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <scriptDesc>
                     <scriptNote>Ashkenazi (French?) square script of the 13th century. Śimḥah bar Yosef: inscribed
                                with his name on folio 271v: חזק ונתחזק שמחה בר יוסף. The word
                                Shelomoh is decorated on folio 276v.</scriptNote>
                  </scriptDesc>
